position overview
hawaiian airlines revenue analytics is seeking a high-performing individual and team player to lead mathematical modeling and optimization project across team department-wide this position provides advanced analytical product and service specializing in creating innovative data-driven decision-support tool to optimize business decision through application of statistical and mathematical modeling
key responsibilities
provide analytical consultation statistical mathematical modeling and solution to achieve business objective
research design develop implement and support decision-science model
conduct research on analytical technique and translate that research into usable and sustainable solution for user of production system
perform data collection data cleaning data validation and reporting task for analytical system and application
perform exploratory data analysis to identify pattern and trend in customer behavior
lead the analysis and validation of statistical forecasting and optimization model
communicate analytical result to business partner and client
serve a technical consultant in the field of operation research data science decision analytics and applied mathematics
design and develops advanced analytical data mining forecasting estimation simulation and or optimization model
provide science calibration support for decision-science model
identify and apply best practice in field of advanced analytics
requirements
minimum requirements
master's degree in statistics operations research econometrics applied mathematics machine learning decision science industrial engineering or related field
5+ year of experience in applying advanced analytics to support business decision yielding measured outcome improvement
expertlevel fluency in applying advance multivariate statistical analysis logistic linear regression decision tree cluster analysis anova to categorize classify and detect relationship in large datasets
proficiency in extracting and cleansing large datasets from different data source
proficiency in programming with knowledge of sql r sas python or other similar language
ability to understand complex business requirement and define key performance metric to measure benefit and communicate complex quantitative analysis in a clear precise and actionable manner
preferred qualification
phd in statistics operations research econometrics applied mathematics machine learning decision science industrial engineering or related field
strong grasp of revenue management theory and concept
experience leading diverse team and interacting with vendor
demonstrated familiarity with the airline or transportation industry
